❓ License FAQ

Q1: Can I use this project at my company?
Yes, but only for non-commercial purposes (e.g., internal learning, prototyping, research). Any commercial use (selling, offering as a paid service, or using in a commercial product) requires a separate license from the copyright holder.

Q2: Can I fork and modify the code?
Yes. You can modify and fork the project for non-commercial use. But if you distribute your modified version, you must also share the source code under the same license (Apache 2.0 + Commons Clause + Derivative Works Clause). for the benefit of the community.

Q3: What does “use at your own risk” mean?
